STEP 9: Trend Clustering service
----------------------------------------------------

Write unit tests first.

Create clusterSignalsIntoTrends(signals): Trend[]

Rules:
- Signals with AI assistant/conversational/search/recommendation tags cluster into:
  “AI-assisted grocery discovery”
- Signals with sponsored/retail media/ad placement tags cluster into:
  “Retail media influence on search outcomes”
- Signals with recipe/meal planning/basket tags cluster into:
  “Recipe-to-cart shopping journeys”
- Signals with transparency/trust/explainability tags cluster into:
  “Trust and transparency in AI recommendations”

Trend scoring:
- likelihoodScore = average signal strengthScore adjusted by number of sources
- confidenceScore = average signal confidenceScore
- impactScore = deterministic mapping by trend type
- horizon:
  - high signal count + high strength → 6–12 months
  - medium evidence → 12–24 months
  - weak evidence → 2–3 years

Test cases:
- Related signals cluster into correct trend.
- Unrelated signals do not cluster.
- Trend has relatedSignalIds.
- Trend includes whatNeedsToBeTrue.
- Trend includes leadingIndicators.
- Trend includes monitoringQuestions.
- Scores are between 0 and 1.
- Horizon is populated.
- Maturity stage is populated.
- Duplicate signals do not create duplicate trends.

Then implement.

Verification:
- Unit tests pass.
- Trend generation deterministic.
- Every trend links back to signals.

